The chamaeleon has no prickles on its leaves. There is however this difference also, that some os these plants have many stems and branches, the thistle for instance, while the cnecos has one stem and no branches. Some are prickly only at the head, the erynge for instance; some, like tetralix and helxine, blossom in summer. Scolymos too blossoms late and long. The acorna is distin- guished (from cnecos)‘¹ only by its reddish colour and richer juice.
